OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FIncreases in household     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fbills kick in for millions 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Rises in a host of essential bills are 
OL,6, now taking effect, adding pressure to  
OL,7, strained budgets - but the lowest      
OL,8, earners are also receiving better pay. 
OL,10,FThe start of April marks the point at  
OL,11,Fwhich council tax, water bills, and    
OL,12,Fsome mobile costs rise, coming just as 
OL,13,Ffood prices are soaring.               
OL,15,FBut the biggest cash increase in the   
OL,16,F24-year history of the minimum wage    
OL,17,Falso comes into force.                 
OL,19,FNearly two million people will receive 
OL,20,F#10.42 an hour from now, a 92p rise.   
